                Trout slices in leche de tigre (a spicy lime and pepper sauce), served Amanto style. 
                Accompanied with corn, crispy sweet potato and chulpi (half popped corn kernels).
              </p>
            </div>
            </BackgroundGradient>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Sopas / Soups -->
    <section class="py-20 px-4 bg-black/10">
      <div class="container mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-16">
          <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-4 gradient-text" data-translate="menu.soups">
            Sopas
          </h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <BackgroundGradient className="p-8">
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex justify-between items-start">
                <div class="flex-1">
                  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold gradient-text">CREMA DE MAÍZ</h3>
                  <p class="text-sm text-foreground/60 mt-1">ANCESTRAL CORN SOUP</p>
                </div>
                <span class="text-xl font-bold gradient-text">S/. 28.00</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-foreground/70 text-sm">
                Receta ancestral de nuestros abuelos basada en el uso del grano del maíz acompañada de habas, 
